# QuickBits Working Rule

## Architecture Map

- `src/` -> Stream Deck plugin TypeScript sources.
- `helper/` -> .NET helper published to `dev.aryapaw.quickbits.sdPlugin/helper/QuickbitsHelper.exe`.
- `triggers/` -> Skydimo trigger apps published into `dev.aryapaw.quickbits.sdPlugin/triggers/`.
- `dev.aryapaw.quickbits.sdPlugin/ui/` -> Property Inspector with local `sdpi-components.js` (do not replace with npm package).
- `dev.aryapaw.quickbits.sdPlugin/imgs/` -> action icons (SVG).

## Non-Negotiable Conventions

- ES modules only: use `import.meta.url`; avoid `__dirname`.
- Keep changes minimal and scoped; do not refactor unrelated areas.
- Respect existing action UUIDs and settings keys unless migration is explicitly requested.
- For helper calls, prefer `child_process.execFile` and preserve `{ success, output }` style responses.
- Do not introduce background services/processes unless user asks.

## Build And Validation

- Primary commands:
  - `bun run build`
  - `bun run build:helper`
  - `bun run build:triggers`
  - `bun run build:plugin`
- For TS-only edits, run `bun run build:plugin` as default validation.
- If build is not run, explicitly report "NOT RUN" and include the exact command.

## Action/UI Rules

- Icons must remain SVG and live under `imgs/actions/{action-name}/`.
- Keep plugin visual behavior aligned with manifest expectations; avoid silent state-model changes.
- Prefer updating key image/title intentionally (`setImage`, `setTitle`) instead of ad-hoc UI mutations.
- Preserve settings persistence behavior in Property Inspector (`setting` attribute contract).

## Spotify Rules

- Keep centralized state flow via `SpotifyState` (single polling loop, shared subscriptions).
- Handle token refresh and `401` recovery without duplicating auth logic in each action.
- Respect `429` backoff behavior; do not add aggressive polling.
- Required Spotify scopes:
  - `user-read-playback-state`
  - `user-modify-playback-state`
  - `user-read-currently-playing`
  - `user-library-read`
  - `user-library-modify`

## Skydimo/Windows Rules

- Trigger apps are foreground WinForms executables; preserve launch expectations (`windowsHide: false` where needed).
- Keep Skydimo toggle behavior based on persisted `screenSyncActive` setting (not live remote state).
- Helper remains self-contained; avoid changes that reintroduce runtime DLL dependencies.
- For system-level key simulation flows, do not replace proven `keybd_event` path without explicit request.
